    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-31T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-31T05:00:00-05:00" n="774"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.918/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-31T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 31, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 31—12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>657. On July 24th the American Peking editor of the <hi rend="italic">Peking
                        Leader</hi>,<note n="80" xml:id="d774fn80">Grover Clark.</note> published in
                    English, was notified by local authorities that Ministry of Interior had ordered
                    censorship of his paper.</p>
                <pb facs="0914" n="770" xml:id="pg_770"/>
                <p>No reason for order was given, but associate editor<note n="81" xml:id="d774fn81"
                        >E. W. Hunter, an American citizen.</note> suggests it possibly is connected
                    with a front-page news article written by him regarding the American Museum of
                    Natural History’s forced abandonment of its Central Asiatic expedition<note
                        n="82" xml:id="d774fn82">Under the leadership of Roy Chapman Andrews of New
                        York. See <ref target="#pg_841">pp. 841</ref> ff.</note> as previously
                    reported to the Department.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Following receipt of order, the paper has sent from it proofs to censor’s
                        office, but these have promptly been stamped and returned. Editor states
                        that there have been no suggestions that all or part of any material
                        prepared for publication should be suppressed or altered and that he does
                        not for the present at least propose to enter any formal protest.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Peking Leader</hi> is incorporated under the laws of
                        Delaware, but its board of directors and stockholders are international in
                        character, including Chinese.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
